WEBVTT

00:00:35.306 --> 00:00:36.641
I…

00:00:39.602 --> 00:00:41.229
passed the interview.

00:00:57.453 --> 00:00:58.371
Rin.

00:00:59.956 --> 00:01:00.999
Congratulations.

00:01:02.167 --> 00:01:05.128
You really earned it.

00:01:15.346 --> 00:01:16.431
Thank you.

00:01:27.650 --> 00:01:29.652
I know that I

00:01:31.446 --> 00:01:33.531
put you in a tough spot…

00:01:35.742 --> 00:01:38.161
and that you thought
really hard about it for me.

00:01:40.622 --> 00:01:42.040
I know it all.

00:01:46.419 --> 00:01:47.754
So…

00:01:49.797 --> 00:01:54.552
I want to treasure that no matter…

00:01:56.554 --> 00:01:58.056
what happens.

00:02:00.183 --> 00:02:01.559
I want to keep it safe with me…

00:02:05.939 --> 00:02:07.398
even when I return to Korea.

00:02:20.995 --> 00:02:23.623
If you feel lonely, don't hide it.

00:02:25.416 --> 00:02:26.417
Okay.

00:02:27.335 --> 00:02:28.503
You too.

00:02:28.586 --> 00:02:30.338
I never hide it.

00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:32.215
You know that, don't you?

00:02:33.299 --> 00:02:34.259
That's true.

00:02:46.187 --> 00:02:47.480
We will…

00:02:49.065 --> 00:02:50.191
be okay.

00:02:53.861 --> 00:02:54.696
Yeah.

00:04:03.973 --> 00:04:06.142
CLOSED FOR PRIVATE EVENT

00:04:06.225 --> 00:04:07.518
Picture time!

00:04:07.602 --> 00:04:09.479
Hurry, hurry! Come on!

00:04:10.396 --> 00:04:12.732
Closer, closer. Okay.

00:04:12.815 --> 00:04:14.400
Okay, say

00:04:14.484 --> 00:04:17.403
-Tanomi!
-Tanomi!

00:04:23.034 --> 00:04:27.246
Actually, having a takoyaki party was
on my bucket list too.

00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:29.582
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:04:29.665 --> 00:04:31.417
-I'm glad we got to do it together.
-Yeah.

00:04:31.501 --> 00:04:32.877
Thanks.

00:04:32.960 --> 00:04:35.505
They're turning perfectly round.

00:04:35.588 --> 00:04:36.422
Yeah.

00:04:36.506 --> 00:04:37.632
This one's burning.

00:04:37.715 --> 00:04:38.716
Ouch!

00:04:39.384 --> 00:04:40.426
That was hot.

00:04:41.552 --> 00:04:42.887
Of course it's hot.

00:04:42.970 --> 00:04:44.889
-It was my bare hand, too.
-No wonder.

00:04:49.519 --> 00:04:50.770
Thank you.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:58.778
The last time we met…

00:05:01.322 --> 00:05:04.200
I'm sorry I was rude to you.

00:05:05.034 --> 00:05:06.828
Oh no, it's nothing.

00:05:08.996 --> 00:05:13.334
-You see, I told you it's hot!
-It's so hot!

00:05:13.918 --> 00:05:15.503
Are you okay?

00:05:15.586 --> 00:05:17.463
Shige, I want to eat one too.

00:05:17.547 --> 00:05:18.381
Sure.

00:05:18.464 --> 00:05:20.174
-This one?
-Rin

00:05:20.258 --> 00:05:22.176
-needed you, it seems.
-Try this one.

00:05:26.973 --> 00:05:30.726
Please take care of Rin from now on too.

00:05:36.858 --> 00:05:39.360
Yes, I will.

00:05:40.403 --> 00:05:42.488
-Jjan.
-Jjan.

00:05:45.241 --> 00:05:46.993
‎Rin, that one is ready to eat.

00:05:47.076 --> 00:05:48.119
Here, Shige.

00:05:48.202 --> 00:05:49.328
Thank you.

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:53.082
So when are you going back?

00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:57.670
The 28th.

00:05:58.296 --> 00:05:59.839
That's so soon!

00:06:02.717 --> 00:06:04.093
I see…

00:06:05.511 --> 00:06:07.138
It'll be lonely without you.

00:06:13.686 --> 00:06:14.562
Sorry.

00:06:17.899 --> 00:06:19.108
It's okay.

00:06:19.192 --> 00:06:21.569
I'm just going to be
a little far away, that's all.

00:06:22.153 --> 00:06:24.197
Nothing else will change.

00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:28.075
I mean, we have social media
and video calling too.

00:06:28.159 --> 00:06:29.243
Yeah.

00:06:29.327 --> 00:06:32.246
Nothing will change between us.

00:06:34.248 --> 00:06:35.958
You two will be okay.

00:06:36.709 --> 00:06:38.794
If you love each other,

00:06:38.878 --> 00:06:41.214
it'll be okay no matter where you are.

00:06:41.297 --> 00:06:42.423
Right?

00:06:43.216 --> 00:06:44.467
Shige…

00:06:44.967 --> 00:06:45.801
Hey,

00:06:45.885 --> 00:06:48.054
I bet you think
those were such wise words.

00:06:48.137 --> 00:06:49.138
I do.

00:06:50.306 --> 00:06:53.643
And so, Rin, come visit us anytime.

00:06:53.726 --> 00:06:57.438
When you feel lonely,
you just need to come visit… me.

00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:00.399
I will.

00:07:01.275 --> 00:07:03.110
-You heard that?
-Oh, Shige…

00:07:13.829 --> 00:07:16.040
-Taiga.
-Yes?

00:07:17.959 --> 00:07:19.669
I'll give this to you.

00:07:20.753 --> 00:07:21.629
What?

00:07:37.979 --> 00:07:41.357
-This is… yours.
-Yeah.

00:07:42.858 --> 00:07:44.151
Make sure you sharpen it.

00:07:45.653 --> 00:07:49.490
Pay more attention to how you sharpen
your knife than how you cut with it.

00:07:54.328 --> 00:07:57.206
Yes. I will use it with the utmost care.

00:08:02.295 --> 00:08:05.089
Thank you very much.

00:08:10.386 --> 00:08:12.638
-Um, Shige…
-Huh?

00:08:13.931 --> 00:08:15.433
If it's not too much trouble,

00:08:15.975 --> 00:08:18.853
may I continue working here
even when I start school?

00:08:18.936 --> 00:08:21.939
Well, I appreciate that you want to,

00:08:22.481 --> 00:08:24.066
but shouldn't you focus on school?

00:08:25.985 --> 00:08:29.447
Tanomi is where my roots are.

00:08:30.156 --> 00:08:34.118
Thanks to you, Shige, and our customers,

00:08:35.828 --> 00:08:37.580
I am who I am today.

00:08:38.247 --> 00:08:41.042
That's why I want to continue helping out

00:08:41.125 --> 00:08:43.044
for as long as I can.

00:08:52.595 --> 00:08:55.348
Well then,
maybe I will take you up on that offer.

00:08:57.141 --> 00:08:59.727
Okay. Thank you very much.

00:09:00.561 --> 00:09:01.395
TANOMI

00:09:01.479 --> 00:09:02.647
HERE ARE THE PHOTOS FROM TODAY! THANK YOU!

00:09:50.361 --> 00:09:52.113
It's already been a year, huh?

00:10:24.520 --> 00:10:25.813
Hello?

00:10:26.439 --> 00:10:28.315
I'm sorry. Were you sleeping?

00:10:28.899 --> 00:10:30.109
No.

00:10:30.901 --> 00:10:32.111
What's up?

00:10:33.612 --> 00:10:34.613
You know…

00:10:36.365 --> 00:10:38.159
There's a place I want to take you.

00:10:41.746 --> 00:10:44.165
So this is where you grew up?

00:10:46.208 --> 00:10:49.545
It's a comfortable and warm place,

00:10:49.628 --> 00:10:50.796
just like you.

00:10:51.422 --> 00:10:52.590
Really?

00:10:55.134 --> 00:10:58.471
It feels strange to be here with you.

00:11:00.055 --> 00:11:02.641
I was always practicing on my own.

00:11:03.267 --> 00:11:05.603
I would use this as my starting line,

00:11:06.771 --> 00:11:08.564
and run downstream.

00:11:11.317 --> 00:11:13.694
I loved running here.

00:11:14.987 --> 00:11:17.948
The wind, the sounds, the scents…

00:11:19.867 --> 00:11:21.785
Everything felt amazing.

00:11:23.245 --> 00:11:26.415
-I want to see you running.
-What?

00:11:27.082 --> 00:11:28.167
That's embarrassing.

00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:30.211
Come on. Just once.

00:11:30.294 --> 00:11:33.088
Okay, let's race to that point.

00:11:33.172 --> 00:11:34.548
There's no way you'd win.

00:11:34.632 --> 00:11:35.925
Sijag!

00:11:39.887 --> 00:11:40.930
You're serious?

00:11:48.812 --> 00:11:49.688
Taiga!

00:11:51.815 --> 00:11:52.858
Wait…

00:12:17.424 --> 00:12:18.384
Rin?

00:12:27.059 --> 00:12:28.185
What's wrong?

00:12:30.187 --> 00:12:31.230
I'm sorry.

00:12:32.481 --> 00:12:35.025
But you were going so far away…

00:13:28.287 --> 00:13:30.623
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

00:13:45.638 --> 00:13:48.932
Taiga is always taking care of me.

00:13:49.642 --> 00:13:51.477
My name is Park Rin.

00:13:55.272 --> 00:13:57.941
Oh, this is…

00:13:58.734 --> 00:14:01.445
no… um…

00:14:02.404 --> 00:14:06.116
It's nothing much, but please enjoy.

00:14:06.200 --> 00:14:07.493
Oh my.

00:14:07.576 --> 00:14:10.287
You didn't have to. Thank you.

00:14:11.830 --> 00:14:14.333
Rin is from Korea,

00:14:14.416 --> 00:14:16.335
and came here to study animation.

00:14:17.670 --> 00:14:21.632
So you're going to work
in the animation field in Japan?

00:14:27.680 --> 00:14:28.847
No.

00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:33.477
Once I graduate,
I plan on working in Korea,

00:14:33.560 --> 00:14:35.396
designing for an advertising company.

00:14:36.271 --> 00:14:37.189
I see…

00:14:37.690 --> 00:14:39.316
Is that right?

00:14:40.776 --> 00:14:43.779
So when are you graduating?

00:14:47.408 --> 00:14:49.410
-This month.
-What?

00:14:50.953 --> 00:14:54.999
So this month you're going back to Korea?

00:14:58.961 --> 00:15:00.004
Yes.

00:15:03.924 --> 00:15:05.259
Um…

00:15:06.427 --> 00:15:07.636
You two are dating, right?

00:15:09.138 --> 00:15:11.348
Yes, we are.

00:15:20.190 --> 00:15:23.527
I'm sorry for making you worried.

00:15:24.194 --> 00:15:27.656
But we made this decision together.

00:15:29.908 --> 00:15:31.285
We came here

00:15:32.453 --> 00:15:34.955
because I wanted to show Rin
the place where I grew up.

00:15:38.959 --> 00:15:40.002
I…

00:15:41.920 --> 00:15:46.175
have a goal now, thanks to Rin.

00:15:48.385 --> 00:15:49.428
The truth is,

00:15:50.637 --> 00:15:53.015
I'm thinking of becoming
a registered dietitian.

00:15:53.974 --> 00:15:55.017
So…

00:15:56.268 --> 00:15:57.978
I'm going to school starting April.

00:15:58.604 --> 00:15:59.855
Wait a second.

00:16:01.356 --> 00:16:02.691
You're going back to school?

00:16:02.775 --> 00:16:05.360
But what about the restaurant?

00:16:06.779 --> 00:16:08.697
The owner was very understanding,

00:16:09.406 --> 00:16:11.492
so I'm going to work
while going to school.

00:16:11.575 --> 00:16:13.327
That's not realistic.

00:16:13.911 --> 00:16:15.287
What if it doesn't work again--

00:16:15.370 --> 00:16:17.039
Even if it doesn't work, again,

00:16:18.123 --> 00:16:19.208
I'll be fine this time.

00:16:21.752 --> 00:16:25.297
Because now I know that
I can always start again.

00:16:40.729 --> 00:16:43.190
RENEWS HIGHEST RANKING

00:16:51.698 --> 00:16:52.699
Taiga.

00:16:53.367 --> 00:16:54.660
You're okay on time?

00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:05.254
I was just thinking about
how hard I worked back then.

00:17:16.306 --> 00:17:18.809
Thank you for having me today.

00:17:18.892 --> 00:17:19.852
My pleasure.

00:17:21.603 --> 00:17:23.105
Next time…

00:17:29.111 --> 00:17:29.945
See you.

00:17:32.239 --> 00:17:33.115
Wait.

00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:42.791
Send me the address
of the place you're working at.

00:17:44.877 --> 00:17:45.836
What?

00:17:46.879 --> 00:17:48.589
They're taking care of you, right?

00:17:50.007 --> 00:17:51.383
When I go to Tokyo,

00:17:52.801 --> 00:17:53.927
I'll pay my respects.

00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:02.686
Okay.

00:18:04.605 --> 00:18:07.149
Thank you, Big Bro.

00:18:17.242 --> 00:18:21.830
When Taiga decided to quit track,

00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:25.584
I was anxious and worried,

00:18:25.667 --> 00:18:27.711
so I said a lot
of unnecessary things to him.

00:18:28.670 --> 00:18:33.050
That has always been bothering me.

00:18:36.345 --> 00:18:40.140
I realized
that I should've had more faith in him,

00:18:40.224 --> 00:18:42.392
and let him follow his own course.

00:18:43.227 --> 00:18:45.938
Seeing him today made me realize that.

00:18:47.272 --> 00:18:48.899
You and Taiga

00:18:48.982 --> 00:18:51.485
will be able to find
what is best for the both of you.

00:18:53.111 --> 00:18:54.571
I am sure.

00:18:56.823 --> 00:18:57.783
Yes.

00:19:02.788 --> 00:19:05.749
Mom, we'll have to leave soon.

00:19:06.333 --> 00:19:08.001
-Take care, you two.
-Thanks.

00:19:08.543 --> 00:19:11.380
Rin, please take care of Taiga.

00:19:12.047 --> 00:19:14.800
Oh, he is always the one
taking care of me.

00:19:26.061 --> 00:19:26.937
I…

00:19:27.729 --> 00:19:29.815
will do my best, one step at a time.

00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:37.531
I'm looking forward to it.

00:19:39.574 --> 00:19:41.201
But don't overwork yourself.

00:20:01.763 --> 00:20:05.559
GRADUATION EXHIBITION

00:20:07.644 --> 00:20:10.063
TOKYO UNIVERSITY OF FINE ARTS
DEPARTMENT OF ANIMATION

00:20:10.147 --> 00:20:13.358
ONIGIRI - PARK RIN

00:20:13.442 --> 00:20:15.110
Back when I first started school,

00:20:16.111 --> 00:20:18.530
I wanted to become an animator,

00:20:19.156 --> 00:20:22.326
but I didn't have anything
specific in mind.

00:20:27.289 --> 00:20:29.583
What do I want to do?

00:20:29.666 --> 00:20:31.293
What am I capable of?

00:20:31.877 --> 00:20:36.214
I didn't know the answer
and was completely lost.

00:20:50.062 --> 00:20:51.646
Thinking back now,

00:20:52.773 --> 00:20:54.983
there were moments
I compared myself to others…

00:20:57.778 --> 00:21:00.572
and moments where I suffered
from self-doubt.

00:21:00.655 --> 00:21:02.449
But all of those moments…

00:21:07.079 --> 00:21:11.958
were very important detours
that I had to make, in a way.

00:21:14.920 --> 00:21:17.339
Just to make one onigiri,

00:21:17.923 --> 00:21:21.134
you need to cook the rice,
prepare the stuffing,

00:21:21.635 --> 00:21:22.677
and wrap it in seaweed.

00:21:36.525 --> 00:21:39.736
Everything is a product
of small, individual steps.

00:21:44.908 --> 00:21:48.245
And what's important
is what kind of outlook

00:21:48.328 --> 00:21:51.373
you have on each and every one
of those steps.

00:21:56.336 --> 00:21:59.756
That is what I learned
over the past two years.

00:22:28.368 --> 00:22:31.121
I hope that this animation

00:22:31.746 --> 00:22:34.374
motivates you to cast a spotlight

00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:37.377
on fleeting moments like these.

00:22:38.920 --> 00:22:42.799
Thank you very much for watching.

00:23:02.652 --> 00:23:06.281
Mom, I just returned the key.

00:23:08.700 --> 00:23:10.660
I'll head to the airport soon.

00:23:43.568 --> 00:23:44.611
Shall we go?

00:23:47.447 --> 00:23:48.365
Yeah.

00:24:13.098 --> 00:24:17.602
NARITA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT

00:24:26.736 --> 00:24:31.283
All right, so we'll send a message
every day when we wake up,

00:24:31.366 --> 00:24:33.201
and we'll do a video call before bed.

00:24:33.285 --> 00:24:34.619
These two are a must, right?

00:24:34.703 --> 00:24:35.537
Yeah.

00:24:35.620 --> 00:24:39.082
As soon as I can take time off,
I'll send you my schedule.

00:24:40.417 --> 00:24:44.796
I think I can visit you
some time during summer break too.

00:24:47.674 --> 00:24:48.800
Well then…

00:24:53.221 --> 00:24:54.431
I guess…

00:24:57.434 --> 00:24:59.019
we're all set?

00:25:09.321 --> 00:25:10.280
Oh, that's right.

00:25:11.906 --> 00:25:12.949
One final thing…

00:25:13.783 --> 00:25:16.119
I mean, it's not "final" but…

00:25:18.663 --> 00:25:21.958
I wanted you to eat this.

00:25:39.851 --> 00:25:40.977
Thank you.

00:25:42.437 --> 00:25:43.438
I'm so happy.

00:25:54.074 --> 00:25:55.283
Thanks.

00:26:11.549 --> 00:26:15.095
What is this called?

00:26:21.393 --> 00:26:25.563
It's shigure-ni
with shishito peppers and beef.

00:26:27.023 --> 00:26:28.274
Shigure-ni…

00:26:30.652 --> 00:26:34.114
It kind of tastes like Korean jang-jorim.

00:26:48.378 --> 00:26:50.964
I'm sorry, we're closed for today.

00:26:51.047 --> 00:26:53.091
TANOMI

00:26:53.174 --> 00:26:54.801
Okay…

00:26:54.884 --> 00:26:58.388
-You eat like you really enjoy the food.
-Joesongham-- I mean, I'm sorry.

00:27:00.807 --> 00:27:03.309
Out of all the onigiri I've had in Japan,

00:27:03.393 --> 00:27:04.769
this is the best.

00:27:08.148 --> 00:27:09.315
The Classic.

00:27:09.941 --> 00:27:13.445
This is like a scene
out of my favorite movie.

00:27:19.242 --> 00:27:21.119
-Bucket list?
-Yes.

00:27:21.828 --> 00:27:24.289
Why don't you make one too?

00:27:24.372 --> 00:27:25.707
When I'm with you,

00:27:26.458 --> 00:27:29.752
I feel like I can move forward.

00:27:34.257 --> 00:27:37.927
Taiga, are you not that good
at keeping in touch?

00:27:39.512 --> 00:27:42.390
When you don't read my messages,

00:27:42.474 --> 00:27:44.893
or a day goes by without a word from you,

00:27:44.976 --> 00:27:47.645
I start to wonder
if you have no interest in me.

00:27:48.313 --> 00:27:49.856
Happy birthday!

00:27:51.733 --> 00:27:53.735
Why didn't you say anything?

00:27:54.777 --> 00:27:55.778
Whatever.

00:27:57.739 --> 00:27:59.324
Maybe it is difficult for two people

00:28:00.241 --> 00:28:02.619
from different backgrounds to be together?

00:28:02.702 --> 00:28:04.370
From now on…

00:28:04.454 --> 00:28:06.998
I want to know more about

00:28:07.665 --> 00:28:08.958
the things you value.

00:28:10.001 --> 00:28:11.044
Thank you.

00:28:13.046 --> 00:28:14.506
I believe

00:28:14.589 --> 00:28:17.258
that your training right now
will not be wasted.

00:28:17.342 --> 00:28:19.677
Just like you said,

00:28:20.428 --> 00:28:24.933
if we try our best to share
everything with each other,

00:28:26.017 --> 00:28:29.020
we won't be lonely
even if we're far apart…

00:28:30.313 --> 00:28:31.397
I think.

00:28:31.481 --> 00:28:33.066
Why didn't you tell me?

00:28:34.025 --> 00:28:34.943
Well…

00:28:35.818 --> 00:28:36.945
Were you hiding it?

00:28:37.612 --> 00:28:39.155
Of course not.

00:28:39.239 --> 00:28:42.408
I wish you would've accepted me,
even just for a second.

00:28:43.701 --> 00:28:46.037
Why don't you get it?

00:28:49.624 --> 00:28:50.583
Sorry.

00:28:51.751 --> 00:28:52.919
I can't keep up with you.

00:29:06.099 --> 00:29:07.392
Your words…

00:29:08.226 --> 00:29:09.435
Your smile…

00:29:10.103 --> 00:29:11.312
Everything about you

00:29:12.063 --> 00:29:13.606
gave me strength.

00:29:16.025 --> 00:29:17.986
I don't want to let you go yet.

00:29:19.571 --> 00:29:21.781
Whether I'm feeling happy, or anything,

00:29:21.865 --> 00:29:23.074
‎FORTUNE

00:29:23.157 --> 00:29:25.368
the first person I think of is you.

00:29:26.744 --> 00:29:28.830
Everything brings me back to you.

00:29:30.540 --> 00:29:32.125
I like you, Taiga.

00:29:33.334 --> 00:29:37.046
I want to stay with you
even after you graduate.

00:29:40.174 --> 00:29:43.261
I want to be with you too.

00:29:52.854 --> 00:29:53.813
Rin…

00:29:55.481 --> 00:29:58.568
You can't stay here, right?

00:30:03.406 --> 00:30:04.282
I'm sorry.

00:30:05.408 --> 00:30:06.910
I didn't want to end things like this…

00:30:06.993 --> 00:30:07.827
I mean,

00:30:09.078 --> 00:30:10.663
I know it's not the end, but…

00:30:12.248 --> 00:30:13.374
But you know…

00:30:16.210 --> 00:30:17.211
I was…

00:30:24.177 --> 00:30:25.595
saved by you.

00:30:28.473 --> 00:30:29.515
Taiga…

00:30:39.734 --> 00:30:40.777
Thank you.

00:30:42.528 --> 00:30:43.947
Thank you so much.

00:31:50.513 --> 00:31:51.597
Hello?

00:31:51.681 --> 00:31:52.765
Hello.

00:31:52.849 --> 00:31:54.517
-Did you eat already?
-Yeah.

00:31:54.600 --> 00:31:55.518
What about you?

00:31:55.601 --> 00:31:56.477
I ate.

00:31:57.020 --> 00:31:58.229
How was your presentation?

00:31:59.397 --> 00:32:00.231
It went well.

00:32:00.815 --> 00:32:02.900
Did you finish your assignment on time?

00:32:02.984 --> 00:32:04.360
I barely made it.

00:32:04.444 --> 00:32:05.486
I'm glad.

00:32:06.320 --> 00:32:07.447
Good work.

00:32:08.489 --> 00:32:09.991
You too.

00:32:12.910 --> 00:32:15.038
-Jjan.
-Jjan.

00:32:27.175 --> 00:32:30.428
I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE YOU

00:32:36.642 --> 00:32:38.186
Happy birthday!

00:32:38.978 --> 00:32:40.229
Rin!

00:32:42.273 --> 00:32:44.817
-Thank you!
-Congratulations.

00:32:44.901 --> 00:32:46.611
I missed you.

00:32:56.871 --> 00:33:01.084
The smell comes from the oil
in between the skin and flesh.

00:33:01.167 --> 00:33:04.629
If you cook it from the skin side first,
it starts to come out.

00:33:04.712 --> 00:33:09.592
As the oil comes out, keep removing it
using something like a paper towel.

00:33:09.675 --> 00:33:12.720
By doing this,
you can get rid of that smell…

00:33:26.234 --> 00:33:28.402
TAIGA: ARE YOU GOING ANYWHERE THIS SUMMER?

00:33:33.074 --> 00:33:34.200
Let's go.

00:33:34.283 --> 00:33:36.202
What should we get? Beer?

00:33:37.787 --> 00:33:39.455
-Sounds good.
-Come on!

00:34:01.519 --> 00:34:03.354
‎VISITING A CAFE WITH A FRIEND

00:34:12.572 --> 00:34:13.489
Excuse me.

00:34:14.574 --> 00:34:15.575
Welcome.

00:34:56.324 --> 00:34:57.867
Here's this month's payment.

00:34:59.702 --> 00:35:00.870
Thank you.

00:35:01.495 --> 00:35:02.496
Okay.

00:35:04.999 --> 00:35:06.375
By the way, I read it.

00:35:06.459 --> 00:35:07.960
Akki's Pachiizm.

00:35:10.338 --> 00:35:11.547
Congrats on your first serialization.

00:35:12.173 --> 00:35:14.258
-You're amazing, Dongsaeng!
-No, I'm not.

00:35:14.342 --> 00:35:16.552
It took me two whole years!

00:35:16.636 --> 00:35:18.429
Being a writer is really tough.

00:35:22.850 --> 00:35:24.977
Hyeongnim, can I take this real quick?

00:35:26.562 --> 00:35:27.647
Hello?

00:35:30.942 --> 00:35:34.320
Oh, I'm so sorry!
This week I'm fully booked.

00:35:34.403 --> 00:35:35.738
Excuse me!

00:35:35.821 --> 00:35:38.199
Two orders of sundae gukbap
and soju please.

00:35:38.824 --> 00:35:39.700
‎Hey!

00:35:39.784 --> 00:35:42.411
How are you doing? Having fun?

00:35:42.495 --> 00:35:43.788
I'm doing well.

00:35:43.871 --> 00:35:46.499
I might be able to apply
for my second visa soon.

00:35:47.792 --> 00:35:49.043
Ivanna!

00:35:50.753 --> 00:35:52.463
Look, she's my roommate.

00:36:01.555 --> 00:36:04.016
Hello. This is Shige.

00:36:05.685 --> 00:36:07.353
I don't know what's going on,

00:36:08.020 --> 00:36:09.647
but I'm glad to see
that you're doing well.

00:36:09.730 --> 00:36:11.357
Yeah. Where's Taiga today?

00:36:11.440 --> 00:36:15.528
Oh, he's pretty busy with his other job.

00:36:16.279 --> 00:36:17.571
Their game is tomorrow,

00:36:17.655 --> 00:36:20.825
so the menu is heavier
on the carbohydrates than usual.

00:36:21.701 --> 00:36:24.662
And to boost the athletes' performance,
we chose

00:36:24.745 --> 00:36:28.165
ingredients and cooking methods that
promote easier digestion and absorption.

00:36:32.211 --> 00:36:33.379
Yes.

00:36:33.879 --> 00:36:35.006
This is good, Taiga.

00:36:35.673 --> 00:36:37.800
All right, let's go with this.

00:36:37.883 --> 00:36:40.136
Okay. Let's start preparing.

00:36:40.219 --> 00:36:41.262
-Yes.
-Yes.

00:36:43.931 --> 00:36:48.060
MAMA'S SEASONAL MUST-TRY DINER
RED CHILI PASTE BULGOGI

00:36:48.144 --> 00:36:53.733
RESTAURANT GARDEN BALAM

00:36:56.777 --> 00:36:57.611
Over here!

00:36:58.195 --> 00:36:59.947
You're late!

00:37:00.031 --> 00:37:01.032
Sorry!

00:37:01.115 --> 00:37:02.992
I'm famished. Let's hurry up and order.

00:37:03.075 --> 00:37:04.452
What do you feel like?

00:37:04.535 --> 00:37:06.078
-I don't know…
-It's hard, huh?

00:37:08.331 --> 00:37:10.624
We survived another week.

00:37:11.208 --> 00:37:12.752
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:37:17.340 --> 00:37:18.758
This is the best!

00:37:19.425 --> 00:37:22.178
I can feel it bring
my whole body back to life!

00:37:24.180 --> 00:37:26.182
This week was crazy, as always.

00:37:26.265 --> 00:37:28.059
Me too.

00:37:28.142 --> 00:37:31.687
But living a fulfilling life
is a good thing.

00:37:31.771 --> 00:37:32.855
True.

00:37:33.481 --> 00:37:34.648
Do you enjoy your job?

00:37:35.775 --> 00:37:36.817
Yeah.

00:37:36.901 --> 00:37:37.860
Please enjoy.

00:37:37.943 --> 00:37:39.570
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:37:41.864 --> 00:37:42.823
This looks good.

00:37:43.824 --> 00:37:45.493
You really like that, don't you?

00:37:47.286 --> 00:37:49.246
Is it because of your ex-boyfriend?

00:38:00.966 --> 00:38:02.343
This is amazing!

00:38:02.426 --> 00:38:04.261
This gimbap is so good!

00:38:04.345 --> 00:38:05.763
Thank you.

00:38:05.846 --> 00:38:07.890
Someone special to me
taught me how to make it.

00:38:24.365 --> 00:38:26.742
THIS DRAMA IS FICTION AND ALL CHARACTERS
AND ORGANIZATIONS ARE FICTIONAL

00:38:26.826 --> 00:38:28.828
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita